%%writefile mymodel.py

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
import pandas as pd

def train():
    data = pd.read_csv("C://batches/online_batch/batch9am/Machine_Learning/diabetes.csv")

    features = data[['Glucose', 'BMI', 'Age']]
    target = data['Outcome']

    X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(features, target, random_state=4)
    model = LogisticRegression()
    model.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    
    return model

%%writefile diabetes.py

from tkinter import *
from mymodel import train

root = Tk()
root.configure(bg="gray")

root.geometry("900x500")

f1 = Frame(root, bg="gray")
f1.pack()
l1 = Label(f1, text="ARE YOU DIABETIC??", bg="gray", fg="black", font=(None, 30))
l1.pack()

l = Label(f1, text="", bg="gray", fg="red", font=(None, 30))
l.pack()

f2 = Frame(root, bg="gray")
f2.pack()

l2 = Label(f2, text="BMI", bg="gray", fg="white", font=(None, 24), padx=30)
l2.grid(row=0, column=0)

e1 = Entry(f2, font=(None, 24))
e1.grid(row=0, column=1)

l3 = Label(f2, text="Glucose", bg="gray", fg="white", font=(None, 24), padx=30, pady=30)
l3.grid(row=1, column=0)

e2 = Entry(f2, font=(None, 24))
e2.grid(row=1, column=1)

l4 = Label(f2, text="Age", bg="gray", fg="white", font=(None, 24), padx=30)
l4.grid(row=2, column=0)

e3 = Entry(f2, font=(None, 24))
e3.grid(row=2, column=1)



def check():
    bmi = float(e1.get())
    glucose = int(e2.get())
    age = int(e3.get())
    
    model = train()
    p = model.predict([[glucose, bmi, age]])
    if p == 0:
        l.configure(text="You are not diabetic")
    else:
        l.configure(text="You ar diabetic")

b1 = Button(f2, text="Submit", fg="black", bg="white", height=3, width=10, font=("monospace", 20, "italic"), command=check)
b1.grid(row=3, column=1, padx=40, pady=20)
root.mainloop()
